In this article, President Donald Trump announces the appointment of Steven Mnuchin as the new Treasury Secretary of the United States. The President congratulates Mnuchin, stating that he is the best person for the job and that he will be a champion for the American people. Mnuchin is praised for his successful career in finance and banking, and his ability to make money in the private sector. The President expresses confidence that Mnuchin will work towards middle-class tax reductions, financial reforms, job creation, and the defense of American manufacturing jobs. Mnuchin is also expected to ensure that Wall Street plays by the rules and to use his skills to benefit American workers. Mnuchin expresses gratitude for the opportunity to serve as Treasury Secretary and pledges to work with the President to grow the economy and create better economic opportunities for all Americans.